<p style="text-align: center;">[EN]<br><br><strong>--- On behalf of Tentamenvoorzieningen Social Sciences --- </strong></p>Dear teacher,<br><br>In 6 weeks (on
  <strong>@{formatDateTime(outputs('ComposeDate'), 'dd-MM-yyyy')}</strong>) the
  <strong>@{item()?['Platform']?['Value']}
    @{item()?['Soort']?['Value']}</strong>
  for <strong>@{item()?['Vaktitel']}</strong> will take
  place. <br>We hereby request you to apply for surveillance
  no later than four weeks in advance to the exam (before: @{formatDateTime(outputs('ComposeDateDeadline'),'D')}) by contacting:
  tentamenvoorziening-sw@uva.nl <br><br>The Examinations Board has
  established the following guideluines regarding the number of surveillants to
  be present during an exam:
<p></p>

<ul>
  <li>&lt;50 candidates: 1 or more surveillant(s)</li>
  <li>50-150 candidates: 2 or more surveillants</li>
  <li>for every 75 candidates on top of this: 1 more surveillant</li>
</ul>
Teachers (coordinator and if necessary tutorial teachers) must be present
during their exam to supervise (s.a. to answer any substantive questions from
students). If additional surveillants are needed, the education desk will
organise a pool of surveillants in cooperation with the program director
(initially consisting of OWI-teachers and AIO's). Before the start of the exam,
teachers welcome the surveillants and provide instructions about the exam in
question.<br><br>In any case, the following people must be
present:
<ul>
  <li>Course coordinator or tutorial teacher</li>
  <li>Student-assistant</li>
</ul>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>For questions or comments, please refer to <i>tentamenvoorzieningen</i> at:
  tentamenvoorziening-sw@uva.nl </strong></p>
<br>
